caption: You don't need to pay anything to enter here. Near this place is Chateau Vincennes, a really big castle. Unfortunately when i visited this area the place was closed, but i could walk in the woods.  This area is really big, and has a lot to offer, especially on the other side, you will find Lac Daumesnil. You won't regret going there.
Optimal for walking, biking, jogging and ... during the day. At night there is another business on = not to recommend ...
Beautiful place to run and walk, surrounded by water, birds, ducks and nature.

A must go, you see many peacocks. The entrance is near the zoo. Just come by metro or tram. no need to take bus. Has a big lake, where you can rent a boat and raw. In spring is so beautiful, there are white flowers that look like snow on the ground. Calm place to relax, walk and enjoy the sun. Google maps directions are not that accurate, but you will find it easy.

My fave jardin/ parc in 20th eme in Paris. It‚Äôs totally free to enter, you can do almost anything you want, jogging, walking, running whether you alone or in a group. Visit the arboretum the river just sitting down alone to contemplate your life, reading a book, kissing a with your lover. But please keep it beautiful as it is. Bois de Vincennes, located on the eastern edge of Paris, is one of the largest green spaces in the city, offering a stunning retreat from the urban hustle. Often referred to as the ‚Äúlungs of Paris,‚Äù this expansive park covers nearly 2,500 acres, making it a haven for nature lovers, joggers, cyclists, and families looking to relax outdoors.  The park‚Äôs diverse landscapes range from sprawling meadows and thick woodlands to picturesque lakes, creating a variety of ecosystems that are home to numerous bird species and wildlife. One of the highlights is the Lac Daumesnil, where visitors can rent boats and float peacefully, surrounded by lush greenery. The Parc Floral is another must-see, especially in spring and summer when the vibrant flower displays are in full bloom. For those interested in history, the Ch√¢teau de Vincennes, a medieval fortress located at the park‚Äôs edge, adds a touch of cultural charm.  Bois de Vincennes is well-equipped with paths for biking and walking, making it an ideal spot for those looking to stay active. There‚Äôs also a small zoo, the Parc Zoologique de Paris, and an equestrian center for horseback riding enthusiasts. The park‚Äôs peaceful atmosphere and size make it feel like a natural escape, despite being just a short metro ride from central Paris.  The park hosts various events throughout the year, from concerts to festivals, adding a lively cultural element to the natural surroundings. Whether you‚Äôre after a peaceful walk, a scenic picnic, or just some fresh air, Bois de Vincennes offers something for everyone, blending the tranquility of nature with the charm of Paris.
Very big and lively park. Jogging, picnic, doing sports, cycling, zoo park etc you can do everything here. Also if you like to study botanics, there are different kinds of parks.
Beautiful park, very big, lots of sitting areas, perfect for picnics or just relaxing.. lots of swans and ducks, recommended for all ages
i would advise against going to this park right now. usually it's pretty and fun, but now there's some construction going on and the bridge is closed off. also a lot of people. but the view is nice
Great afternoon watching le trot (Harness rating). A great pizza from Tony, fantastic view of the racing, beautiful horses made a lovely day out even tho the weather was full and wet.

What a great place, almost in the middle of the city! ‚ù§Ô∏è  The park is really really big! Inside is a huge lake with ducks, swans and geese and peacocks!  The place is great not only for sport but also for relaxing. Especially that grass looks like a carpet!  It's definitely one of my favourite places in Vincennes!

Beautiful and huge park on the outskirts of Paris. Visited in August 2020 and not much grass to sit on (lots of dryness around here). Nevertheless, with the lake and endless options of things to do, it's a well equipped and accessible hang out place, which is also great for a run. Not much paved roads, so take.it into consideration when bringing a stroller.

If you live or are visiting nearby, I highly recommend running or riding through the Vincennes Woods. It‚Äôs a beautiful escape from the city with tall trees and winding trails. If you want to get lost in nature, this is the place. If you want to find the city again, just use your GPS. üòä ‚Ä¶
It's very big and beautiful.  There are lots of picnic spots. The flower gardens are pretty and huge place for the kids of all ages to play. Highly recommended
The best park you can visit in Paris. You need to take time for a walk, you can see so many  birds species.

Lovely peaceful green setting in Paris. Second year on the run visiting Porte Doree and this park is a lovely place to unwind after visiting the many busy Paris landmarks. Great to see an albino Peacock on this visit to the park too.
Beautiful place to hanging out with friend
Best Park in/around Paris area. Picnic area for families and naturist area, also for those interested in horse riding, cycling and tennis.

Amazing park, it has everything, calm and quiet corners, big promenades to walk, bike, or run. It also has places for the velib bikes a coffee shop/cantine to drink something by the lake. It is so clean and taken care of that you get away from the city in the best way

Spectacular park on the eastern edge of Paris. Lovely landscaped scenery everywhere, well-tended gravel walkways (with four scenic artificial lakes), gardens, a zoo, a chateau, a temple, room to roam (it's the largest public park in the city). Fantastic history, if you care to look it up. Easy access from three Metro stops. A treasure.

Beautiful, serene, massive and just absolutely amazing. The place is huge! You can play sports, have a picnic, go into the woods and walk and breathe the fresh air. You can sunbathe, you can practically do whatever your heart desires. This place is so big that you don‚Äôt have to worry about it getting too crowded. You can find multiple spots where you can have your complete privacy. Just a great place!  So GREEN!!

This place is highly recommended to people who likes sports and nature. If you want to be in harmony with nature come to this place. The only negative aspect here is that you can notice that people who walk with their dogs are not responsible for what their pets do.
I really love this area! So does my dog! I usually take him to the rugby field next to the triangle that‚Äôs falsely called Polygon and we enjoy the nature.

This park is beautiful with lots of flowers and different exhibits including a bonsai room, Jurassic room, and other spots like 2 cafe's and overall a tranquil environment. The bathrooms are clean and well organized as well as the rest of the park.
Lovely place to go for a walk, have a picnic with friends or tide your bike for hours. So peaceful yet full of life. I love it üòª ‚Ä¶
The place was a nice park to jog/walk around. Very refreshing! Not too many big cities offer escapes like this one! Definitely recommend to visit.

Beautiful place, very big so perfect to walk, do some sport, picnic, or just chill. Easy to get by metro line 1 or RER A (stop ch√¢teau de Vincennes), line 6 (stop Daumesnil) or line 8 (stop libert√©) these two if you want to go to Daumesnil's Lake  There's another lake named Minimes which I prefer since it is more quiet and less crowded.  I recommend to visit also the city's garden (parc floral). It's beautiful and the entrance fee is 2 or 3 euros (it's free from October to Mars). In August - September they have a Dahlias exposition : totally worth it.

Huge park, if you like nature and lots of walk or exercise (running/jogging) you would love this place.  Probably the biggest one not very far from Paris. Really enjoyed the walk for few hours here. Great place for walking, running, relaxation, outdoor activities. I would revisit if I have chance again for sure.
Splendid view.. Boating is must .

Huge Park with a few beautiful lakes. The thing that makes it different is tgat you xan actually take a row boat in the lake.. Which is a lot of fun and a hreat exercise.  The park also has a circus but not always opertaional.. And a botanical garden which I didn't get the chance to visit since the park was so big.  Very relaxing place to spend an afternoon.
The zoo animals were hiding...the tropical house was great...more like a park than a place to see animals.

I visited this park twice during my morning runs, while visiting Paris. What a special place this is!! It has a quite large pond and, in the mornings, it's quite a calm and relaxing spot. Lot's of fellow runners too.
It's a beautiful park. I recommend visiting it and walking through it alone or with company

Superb place for spending whole day soaking good sun and enjoying the lovely views of a pond, greenery and nature at it's best.  These gardens are adjoining the Paris zoo. There is a fantastic play area for the kids with lots of space , zip line , sand pit, slides and swing set. We had a good picnic and plan to visit again too.

Bois de Vincennes park was located directly across the street from my favorite hotel I stay in while in Paris (MOTEL ONE) and is quite large and NON TOURISTY! Incredible views everywhere and there is a BUDDHIST TEMPLE and zoo in the park along with waterways to do some boating.It is certainly a great place to spend an afternoon! I visit this park everytime I'm in Paris....highly recommended. Kirk Regalia Lauderdale by the Sea,  Florida U.S.A.
A big, beautiful and amazing park, suitable for families to picnic, for child and the best for sport and running. There is an outstanding lake inside with docks, geese and swans.
Weather you're walking, boating, camping or just feeding the birds and ducks around the park, for me is one of the best parks in Paris!
Best park ever eastside Paris! Zoo, lake, trail running, hill, wooden boat, birds.... Have a break come and relax here
